snippet.textDisplay:
03:04 the moment Maaz appeared on the screen my heart skipped a beat😍 and the nostalgia, the love, the utmost admiration all hit at once with that soothing voice of Jaffer❤ Choti Choti Khushiyan :') These guys are a vital part of our BACHPAN. Rarely you come across artists who are equally relatable through your teen years to adulthood. Thank you Kaavish for being who you are and making an exceptionally good, soulful music to let us express ourselves when words fall short! Wishing you both success and happiness. 
PS: congratulations Abdul Hannan on your debut coke studio song! People are appreciating the underrated kaavish without taking away anything from you. Keep up the good work👍🏻

snippet.textDisplay:
I think the very end of the song holds so much power. With Abdul - the voice of Despair until that point - humming the tune of the voice of Hope packs such a punch, driving in the idea that even in times of complete darkness, lies the lone, tiny flame of hope waiting to found, nurtured, carried and then to lead. 
What a wonderful composition AND set design (as is the case for every song this season)! Love from India. 💕
